*** Using Wallpaperfun
Put in a folder with .JPG images and run.

*** Requires
.net 3.5
winapi (user32.dll)

*** Tested on
Windows Vista

*** IDE
Visual Studio 2010

*** What it does
Searches "Start in" folder for .jpg images and sets a random one as background image.
If a switch/command line parameter %1 is present, it will attempt to set that as background instead.

*** Warnings
Can only run in user mode, do not start with System or Network Service accounts.